[gd_scene load_steps=3 format=3 uid="uid://b0embergrave_stratum2_boss_room"]

; W3-T7 Stage 5 — Stratum2BossRoom scene (ticket 86c9y7ygj Part D).
;
; Arena topology per Uma `palette-stratum-2.md` §5.5 + W3-T7 Stage 5
; dispatch brief: ~32×24 tiles (1024×768 world units), Sentinel plinth
; in arena center (512, 384), four cardinal walls fully enclosing the
; arena during the fight per `room-gate` LOCKED convention. No
; intermediate ports during Stage 5 — the door trigger sits at the
; south port (entry) and the StratumExit at the north port (exit, locks
; until boss defeat).
;
; Floor color: Color(0.07, 0.06, 0.09, 1) — same near-black floor as S1
; BossRoom for cross-boss tonal consistency. The S2 boss arena reads as
; "the same archive lit at the same depth"; Uma's S2 stratum-palette
; (cooler hue family per palette-stratum-2.md §2) sits on the wall and
; mob silhouette colors, not on the floor.
;
; Wall color: Color(0.12, 0.09, 0.14, 1) — same dim-purple wall tone as
; S1 BossRoom. Stage 5 placeholder; future tile-art ticket can swap to
; S2-specific tilemap.
;
; Wall thickness: 32 px top + 32 px on left/right/bottom — generous
; thickness so the wall sprites read distinctly against the floor at
; arena scale. The collision shapes match the visible sprite extents.
;
; Cross-references:
;   scripts/levels/Stratum2BossRoom.gd (controller)
;   scenes/levels/Stratum1BossRoom.tscn (S1 precedent — same wall pattern)
;   team/uma-ux/palette-stratum-2.md §5.5 "Boss-arena note"

